<topic id="e0846711-419c-11e1-9d4f-002421116fb2" revisionNumber="1">
	<developerSDKTechnologyOverviewTechnologySummaryDocument
	  xmlns="http://ddue.schemas.microsoft.com/authoring/2003/5"
	  xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">

		<introduction>
			<para>
				The <token>DA</token> API reproduces and extends the features of the <token>MA</token> API.
			</para>
			<para>
				It consists of two main components:
			</para>
			<list class="bullet">
				<listItem>
					<para>
						A <token>COMname</token> (<token>COM</token>)
						<newTerm>Server</newTerm> that allows multiple applications, called <newTerm>clients</newTerm>
						or <newTerm>client applications</newTerm>,
						to access its animation, input, and output services at
						the same time. A client can be any application that connects to the <token>DA</token>
						server's <token>COM</token> interfaces.
					</para>
					<para>
						As a <token>COM</token> server, the <token>DA</token> server automatically
						starts only when a client application uses its <token>COM</token> interfaces
						and connects to it. It remains running until all clients close their connections.
						When no connected clients remain, the <token>DA</token> server automatically shuts down.
					</para>
				</listItem>
				<listItem>
					<para>
						An <token>ActiveXCtl</token>
						that makes it easy to access <token>DA</token>'s services from programming languages
						that support the <token>ActiveXInt</token>.
					</para>
					<para>
						The control can be <link xlink:href="e084673a-419c-11e1-9d4f-002421116fb2#connected">
							<token>connected</token>
						</link> to the server, allowing <token>Agent</token> characters to be shared
						among multiple applications. It can also run <link xlink:href="e084673a-419c-11e1-9d4f-002421116fb2#standalone">
							<token>standalone</token>
						</link>,
						providing <token>Agent</token> characters that are private to a specific application.
						This is a new feature of <token>DA</token> that is not supported by <token>MA</token>.
					</para>
					<para>
						The control also allows <token>DA</token> to provide it's character animation services
						<link xlink:href="e084673a-419c-11e1-9d4f-002421116fb2#contained">
							<token>contained</token>
						</link> within a <newTerm>child</newTerm>
						window of a <newTerm>client application</newTerm>'s window. This is a new feature of
						<token>DA</token> that is not supported by <token>MA</token>.
					</para>
				</listItem>
			</list>
			<para>
				See the <token>DA</token>&#160;<link xlink:href="e0846750-419c-11e1-9d4f-002421116fb2">Server</link> and <link xlink:href="e0846730-419c-11e1-9d4f-002421116fb2">Control</link> interfaces for more information on the specific API.
			</para>
			<para>
				In addition to supporting stand-alone programs written for <token>Windows</token>,
				<token>DA</token> can be scripted to support <link xlink:href="e0846736-419c-11e1-9d4f-002421116fb2">Web pages</link>,
				provided that the browser supports <token>COMauto</token> or the <token>ActiveXInt</token>.
				<token>MSIE</token> and other browsers include
				support for <token>ActiveXCtls</token> as well as scripting languages that you can use
				to program <token>DA</token>.
			</para>
		</introduction>
